Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addSdpGroupMember(25.10)                              addSdpGroupMember(25.10)

Name
       addSdpGroupMember  - Adds an object or member to an existing structured
       data path (SDP) group

Syntax
       addSdpGroupMember

       [-help]

       -group <group_name>

       -object <object_name_list>

       [-orientation <orientStr>]

       [-before <refObject> | -after <refObject>]

       Adds an object or member to an  existing  structured  data  path  (SDP)
       group. The added object can be an instance or another SDP group.

       The  addSdpGroupMember  command enables you to create a structured data
       path using TCL commands. You do not need to learn SDP  relative  place-
       ment format for creating a data path.

       Before adding a member to an SDP group, you should have:

              * Imported the design

              * Created  an  SDP  group.  For more information, see createSdp-
                Group.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each addSdpGroupMember parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man addSdpGroupMember.

       -after <refObject>
              Adds  the  SDP group or object after the specified reference ob-
              ject.

       -before <refObject>
              Adds the SDP group or object before the specified reference  ob-
              ject.

       -group <group_name>
              Specifies  the name of the SDP group to which you are adding the
              member.

       -object <object_name_list>
              Specifies the name of the object(s)  to  be  added  to  the  SDP
              group.

       -orientation <orientStr>
              Specifies  the  orientation  to  be  set for the object. You can
              specify orientation as one of  the  following:  R0,  R90,  R180,
              R270, MX, MY, MX90, MY90

              Note:  If  you  do not specify this parameter, the object has R0
              orientation (no rotation) by default.

Examples
              * The following example adds the DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST  instance
                to  the  SDP group sdpGrp1. The instance is rotated 90 degrees
                counter-clockwise.

                addSdpGroupMember -group sdpGrp1 -object DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST
                -orientation R90

              * The     following     examples     adds      two      objects,
                DTMF_INST/tdsp_core_inst/inst1                             and
                DTMF_INST/tdsp_core_inst/inst2, to the sdpGrp1 group.

                addSdpGroupMember        -group        sdpGrp1         -object
                {DTMF_INST/tdsp_core_inst/inst1
                DTMF_INST/tdsp_core_inst/inst2}

